CI is failing on PR #405 with: 'MicroVM reel-life-0: interface vm-reel-0 is not of type bridge and therefore should not have a bridge option defined.'

The previous fix agent incorrectly added 'bridge = "br-reel"' to the TAP interface in modules/reel-life/default.nix. The microvm.nix schema does not allow the 'bridge' attribute on type = "tap" interfaces — the 'bridge' attribute requires type = "bridge".

Fix: In modules/reel-life/default.nix, change the interface definition from:
  type = "tap";
  id = "vm-reel-0";
  mac = "02:00:00:00:01:01";
  bridge = "br-reel";

To:
  type = "bridge";
  id = "vm-reel-0";
  mac = "02:00:00:00:01:01";
  bridge = "br-reel";

That is the ONLY change needed. Do not modify anything else in the file — the secrets ownership and allowed users comment from the previous commit are correct.

After fixing, run 'nix flake check' or 'nix-instantiate --parse modules/reel-life/default.nix' to verify the Nix expression is valid.
